text.section:
Except as otherwise provided in § 10-226 of the State Government Article, and subject to the notice and hearing requirements in subsection (c) of this section, the Board may deny, refuse to renew, suspend, or revoke a license if the applicant or licensee:
Violates any provision of this title or any regulation adopted under this title;
Fraudulently or deceptively obtains or attempts to obtain a license for the licensee or for another person;
Fraudulently or deceptively uses a license;
Commits any gross negligence, incompetence, or misconduct while practicing marine contractor services;
Fails to comply with the terms of a tidal wetlands authorization issued under § 16-202 or § 16-307 of this article;
Violates any provision of, or regulations adopted under, § 16-202 or § 16-307 of this article; or
In the Chesapeake and Atlantic Coastal Bays Critical Area, as defined under § 8-1802 of the Natural Resources Article, fails to comply with:
The terms of a State or local permit, license, or approval; or
Any State or local law, an approved plan, or other legal requirement.
